<Flashcard id="elixir-1" tags={["Elixir"]} source="elixir.astro" priority={50}>
    <Fragment slot="front">
        How are lower arity functions usually implemented?
    </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="back">
        Lower arity functions are usually implemented by calling higher arity
        functions with default values for the additional arguments.
        <CodeBlock
            lang="elixir"
            code={`defmodule Greeter do
  # A lower-arity function delegates to a higher-arity one with a default value
  def greet(name), do: greet(name, "Hello")

  def greet(name, greeting), do: "#{greeting}, #{name}!"
end

# Examples
Greeter.greet("Sam")
# => "Hello, Sam!"

Greeter.greet("Sam", "Hi")
# => "Hi, Sam!"`}
        />
    </Fragment>
</Flashcard>
